<italic toggle="yes">rspatialdata</italic> have been created using the open-source R Project for Statistical Computing (RRID:SCR_001905)
<sup><xref rid="ref7" ref-type="bibr">7</xref></sup> and a number of R packages that allow us to download spatial data corresponding to specific geographic regions and periods of time, as well as to manipulate and visualize the data. Here, we provide a description on how to install the statistical software R and R packages. Then, we show an example on how to download and visualize one of the datasets presented in the website, namely, maximum temperature data. The complete code for all the tutorials can be found at the
